> I suppose then that your compiler doesn't define `__INTEL_COMPILER` ? According to the [predef docs](https://sourceforge.net/p/predef/wiki/Compilers/) the Intel compiler generally does...

No, it does:
```shell
‚ùØ cat helloworld.c
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
   printf("Hello, World!\n");
#ifdef __INTEL_COMPILER
   printf("I run Intel!\n");
#endif
   return 0;
}
‚ùØ icc helloworld.c && ./a.out
Hello, World!
I run Intel!
‚ùØ clang helloworld.c && ./a.out
Hello, World!
‚ùØ
```
